hping3
TCP/IP packet assembler and analyzer

Stress Testing
Description
hping3 is a network tool able to send custom TCP/IP packets and display target replies. Used for firewall testing, port scanning, and network testing.

Installation / Check
Check if installed:

which hping3
Install command:

sudo apt install hping3
Basic Syntax
hping3 [options] <target>
Common Commands
Command	What it does	When to use	Risk
hping3 -S -p 80 target

SYN packet to port 80	Test port response	
hping3 --flood -S -p 80 target

SYN flood	Stress testing (authorized)	
hping3 -1 target

ICMP ping	Basic connectivity	
hping3 -S --scan 1-1000 target

Port scan	Find open ports	
hping3 -S -p 80 --spoof 1.2.3.4 target

Spoofed source	Test firewall rules	
Step-by-Step Guide
1
Choose target
2
Select packet type (SYN/UDP/ICMP)
3
Set port and options
4
Run hping3
5
Analyze responses
Understanding the Output
Shows sent packets and received responses with timing and flags.

Important Warnings
•
Flooding is illegal without permission
•
Can crash systems
•
Use only on authorized targets
⚠️ Use Kali Linux tools only on systems you own or have written permission to test. Unauthorized hacking is illegal and can result in criminal charges.
